The paper deals with the problem of cyber-insurance for Internet security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which suggests the possibility of game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT) being relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of choosing the right type of cyber-insurance contract, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
